        <h2 style="font-size: 40PX;">WELCOME TO FAMBONGLHO WILDLIFE SANCTUARY</h2>
        <p> Fambong Lho Wildlife Sanctuary is a hidden gem in Pakyong district Sikkim, that offers visitors a deep connection with nature's beauty. Nestled at an altitude of around 1,600 to 2,400 meters, this sanctuary is a paradise for wildlife enthusiasts and nature lovers. The sanctuary is home to a rich diversity of flora and fauna, including rare species like the red panda, Himalayan black bear, and various birds such as the Himalayan griffon vulture and colorful pheasants. Visitors can explore its lush forests, dense rhododendron groves, and alpine meadows through scenic trekking trails. The sanctuary offers stunning views of the surrounding mountains, including Kanchenjunga, and is a perfect place to immerse in the untouched beauty of the Eastern Himalayas. Whether you're a wildlife photographer, a trekker, or simply seeking peace amidst nature, Fambong Lho Wildlife Sanctuary offers a truly enriching experience.






        </p>

